<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, May 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- An Israeli Soldier was wounded in an attack by
Lebanese guerrillas in south Lebanon Thursday night, a security
source said.
</P>
<P>
The soldier was slightly injured when his outpost in the
central sector of the Israeli occupied border zone was hit by
guerrillas' hand-grenades, the source added.
</P>
<P>
There has been no group claiming responsibility for the assault.
(BC-Lebanon-Israeli-Wounded)
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cypriot Minister of Commerce, Industry and Tourism
Nicos Rolandis said Friday that the Czech Republic and Cyprus will
make efforts to promote their ties in economic, trade, and tourism
fields.
</P>
<P>
Rolandis made the remarks after he met with his Czech
counterpart Miroslav Gregr, who along with Czech Finance Minister
Ivo Svoboda arrived here Thursday for a three-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the importance of promoting bilateral economic
ties, Rolandis said that "they also have a political dimension."
(BC-Cyprus-Czech-Ties)
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey's central-left Democratic Left Party (DSP)
and right-wing Nationalist Movement Party (MHP) Friday held
"positive" talks for the formation of coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Following the talks between the DSP and MHP, DSP leader and
prime minister-designate Bulent Ecevit told reporters that he had
proposed a coalition partnership to MHP leader Devlet Bahceli.
</P>
<P>
Bahceli told reporters that he would respond to the DSP
proposal after meeting with his party group on Saturday.
(BC-Turkey-Government)
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- A Chinese leader said on Friday that Beijing and Cairo
have established sincere and solid friendship on the basis of
mutual respect and understanding since setting up diplomatic ties
in 1956.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival at Cairo International Airport for a six-day
official visit, Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) Li Ruihuan said
in a written speech that the friendship between the peoples of
China and Egypt goes back to ancient times.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Li Ruihuan visits Egypt, the last stop
of his current Asian and African tour which has already taken him
to South Korea, the United Arab Emirates and Oman.
(BC-Egypt-China-Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
