<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Govt to Assist Disabled People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Deputy Speaker of the
House of People's Representatives Petrol Oalango said Friday the
Ethiopian government is making efforts to help handicapped people
become full beneficiaries of their socio-economic and political
rights.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting organized to discuss the U.N. convention
on the rights of the handicapped here, the deputy speaker said
that the Ethiopian constitution guarantees the rights of
physically and mentally impaired people.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted Petrol as saying that the
proclamation providing for equal job opportunities and the
adoption of the U.N. convention are living testimonies of the
government's commitment to the welfare of the handicapped.
</P>
<P>
He said a program designed to facilitate measures being taken
to rehabilitate disabled persons has been adopted.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on his part, the president of the Federation of the
Association for the Handicapped, Berihun Girmay said that his
federation is endeavoring to improve the life and guarantee the
rights of the handicapped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
