<HEADLINE> S. African Businessmen Explore Opportunities in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- A South African business delegation
has arrived in Uganda to explore possible trade and investment
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is from the South African Foundation, a
consortium of private companies, according to a press release
issued Friday evening by the President's Office.
</P>
<P>
President Yoweri Museveni received the delegation at State
House here Friday and briefed his guests about the political and
economic achievements Uganda has made since independence.
</P>
<P>
At the function also attended by Finance Minister Gerald
Sendaula, Museveni gave them a comprehensive breakdown of the
business opportunities in Uganda and enumerated the various
aspects of Uganda's natural resource base.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, accompanied by South African High Commissioner
to Uganda Raymond Mhlaba, said it came to Uganda because of the
significant progress the Ugandan government has made in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
The trade delegation, which arrived here last weekend, is
interested in agro-processing industry, commercial farming and
trade. Uganda's bilateral trade with South Africa has been
increasing over the past few years. It mainly imports machinery,
household utilities from South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
