<HEADLINE> Russia Lashes out at NATO Attack on Belgrade Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia Friday protested
against the NATO bombing of a Belgrade hospital, saying that this
act will undermine the ongoing effort to seek a political
settlement to the Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
Sergey Lavrov, Russian permanent representative to the United
Nations, told reporters, "We protest against this action and we
state that this so-called mistake occurring daily."
</P>
<P>
"The only way to stop this tragedy is to stop the bombing and
to start concentrating on the efforts to achieve a political
settlement," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Paradoxically, just as we try to achieve a political
settlement, the bombing intensifies. I hope this is not a
deliberate attempt (to) undermine the political settlement
efforts," he said.
</P>
<P>
"But objectively, what is going on in the sky of Yugoslavia not
only doesn't help the efforts to achieve a political settlement,
but make those efforts much more difficult," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian ambassador echoed the position of the the Russian
Foreign Ministry, which "reiterates its strong disapproval of the
criminal actions" of NATO raids on Belgrade Hospital Wednesday
night.
</P>
<P>
The attack killed 4 people and wounded 15 others, including two
women who were delivering, Lavrov said.
</P>
<P>
Lavrov voiced his protest against the NATO strikes before the
U.N. Security Council is scheduled to meet on Kosovo at 3:00 p.m.
EST.
</P>
<P>
Russia is stepping up its efforts as a mediator to seek a
political solution to the Kosovo crisis, which broke out in
February last year after ethnic Albanians have been fighting with
Serbs for independence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
