<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe
will leave Harare Sunday for Kenya to attend the fourth summit of
the Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA), the
Foreign Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting of the COMESA Authority of Heads of State and
Government, the last before a Free Trade Area is launched on
October 31, 2000, will review progress made in the reduction and
elimination of tariff and non- tariff barriers by member states,
the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
COMESA member states agreed to reduce the tariffs to zero
percent at the third summit held in Kinshasa, capital of the
Democratic Republic of Congo, las June.
</P>
<P>
Mugabe will be accompanied by Foreign Minister Stan Mudenge and
 some other senior Zimbabwean government officials. He will
return Tuesday. 
