<HEADLINE> Polish MPs Call for Stop of Bombing on Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Polish parliamentarians signed on
Friday a draft resolution calling for a stop of NATO bombing on
Yugoslavia and a political settlement of the Kosovo crisis through
talks.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution, prepared by 119 members of the 460-seat
parliament from the Democratic Left Alliance and the Polish
Peasant Party, had been presented to the speaker of the House of
Representatives, the Polish Press Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The document said that the NATO air raids on Yugoslavia had not
achieved the expected aim and, on the contrary, caused many tragic
incidents. It warned that "serious and long-standing international
consequences could be possible if situation got out of control."
</P>
<P>
"The Polish Parliament demands that justice be given to the
ethnic Albanians in Kosovo and the (NATO) military action be
halted. We believe that even the hardest problem should be solved
through negotiations," it said.
</P>
<P>
The draft resolution said that it was still possible that a
limited bombing could speed up the adoption of a U.N. Security
Council resolution. It also called on the Yugoslav government to
withdraw its forces from Kosovo in a firm and effective manner.
</P>
</TEXT>
