<HEADLINE> Six Killed in Road Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Six persons were killed and 40 others
were injured, with 10 of them critically, when a passenger bus
collided head-on with a truck on Dhaka-Khulna highway Friday
afternoon, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The passenger bus from western Bangladesh's Faridpur district,
which was heading toward Magura, some 110 kilometers southwest of
here, collided with a loaded truck coming from the opposite
direction, and the badly damaged truck fell into the roadside
ditch, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver and two other persons on the truck died on the
spot.
</P>
<P>
The injured were sent to nearby hospitals, where three of them
died and the condition of ten were critical, according to the
reports. 
</P>
