<HEADLINE> UN Chief Recommends to Extend Mandate of UNDOF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General Kofi
Annan on Friday recommended that the mandate of the United Nations
Disengagement Observer Force (UNDOF) be extend for another period
of six months.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the Security Council, Annan said the ceasefire
between Israel and Syria had been maintained during the past six
months without serious incident.
</P>
<P>
But the U.N. chief said UNDOF was facing a serious funding
problem because of unpaid assessment and appealed to U.N. members
to pay their assessment promptly in full and to clear all
remaining arrears.
</P>
<P>
The 1,048-member UNDOF was established in May 1974 to supervise
a ceasefire and troop disengagement between Syrian and Israeli
armies on the Golan Heights.
</P>
<P>
The current mandate of UNDOF will expire on May 31, 1999.
</P>
</TEXT>
