<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia, Switzerland, Greece to Set up Humanitarian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia, Switzerland and
Greece have decided to set up "FOCUS" Project to combine their
efforts on the delivery and distribution of emergency humanitarian
assistance on the territory of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia
(FRY), a press release from the Russian Mission to the United
Nations said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The press release, being distributed here, said that the three
countries made the decision "with the view to providing
humanitarian assistance to the affected population of FRY."
</P>
<P>
On April 28, the Steering Group on humanitarian response was
set up to carry out the project.
</P>
<P>
The main targets of the "FOCUS" Project are to provide direct
humanitarian assistance to the affected population of FRY,
including Kosovo, a Serbian province, to provide transport
facilities (air and automobile) for delivery of humanitarian goods
to the camps of refugees from Kosovo, said the news release.
</P>
<P>
The three-nation project was designed to ensure security
measures for trucks convoys delivering humanitarian supplies to
the refugee camps, and in the course of aid supplies dropping
operations, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The three countries also invited other nations and
international organizations for cooperation in the framework of the
"FOCUS" Project.
</P>
<P>
For implementing the project, a Trust Fund for donations from
other countries has been established. The contributions made
will be administered by the Steering Group.
</P>
<P>
On May 8-12, three convoys to Scopje, Procople and Belgrade
delivered 86 tons of foodstuffs and medicines, out of those 21
tons of Swiss-donated cargoes were shipped to Pristina, the
release said, adding relief cargoes from Greece were also brought
to Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
"Totally in the "FOCUS" framework mobile truck units delivered
127 tons of supplies," the release said. "Preparatory work is
under way as to delivery of foodstuffs to Kosovo by air."
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-led NATO, under the pretext of humanitarianism,
unilaterally bombed Yugoslavia, creating serious humanitarian
disaster and a large exodus of refugees from Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
