<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Petrochemical Exports Earn 452 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Iran earned 452 million U.S. dollars
from petrochemical exports in last Iranian calendar year (ended on
March 20), Managing Director of the National Iranian Petrochemical
Industry (NIPI) Mohammad Reza Nematzadeh announced on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Nematzadeh said that the country has planned to boost the
figure to 600 million dollars in the current Iranian year, the
Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Putting Iran's petrochemical production at 11.1 million tons
last Iranian year, he predicted that the figure would reach 12.5
million tons in the current Iranian year.
</P>
<P>
The NIPI chief said that 10 Iranian petrochemical firms have
obtained the certificate ISO 9,000 and three others have been
nominated to receive the certificate.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran produces 0.4 percent of the global
petrochemical output, occupying 0.45 percent of global exports.
</P>
<P>
Iran has planned to raise its production to 1.2-1.4 percent
of the global output and to account for 2.5 to 3 percent of
global exports in petrochemical sector by the year 2005, the
official added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
