<HEADLINE> China to Improve Service of Tourist Guides </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- All those who want to be tourist
guides will have to pass a national qualification examination as
of October 1st so as to ensure the quality of the services they
provide.
</P>
<P>
The requirement is included in the Regulations on Tourist
Guides promulgated by the State Council recently.
</P>
<P>
Certificates will be issued to those who pass the exams which
gives them approval to do their job within the framework of the
law.
</P>
<P>
The regulations aim at protecting the legitimate interests of
both tourists and tourist guides, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The 27-article regulations also stipulate that guides should
not engage in any fraudulent behavior affecting their customers,
or they will face penalties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
