<HEADLINE> China Improves Protection of Women's Employment Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China has dramatically improved
the employment rate and job security standards of women and
boosted the insurance related to childbearing.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yazhi, Vice Minister of Labor and Social Security, made the
remarks today at a national conference on women and children,
which opened here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of women staff and workers amongst the urban
workforce has increased annually by 0.1 percent, according to Liu.
</P>
<P>
She said that the wide introduction of the labor contract
system has provided lawful protection of the rights of all workers
including women.
</P>
<P>
Liu explained that departments involved in labor rights
protection have battled against those enterprises that refuse to
sign or violate the labor contracts in various ways, and she urges
those enterprises to deal with disputes involving women workers in
a lawful way.
</P>
<P>
Liu also confirmed that the reform of insurance for
childbearing has been promoted nationwide in 26 provinces and
cities, and more than 27 million women workers have bought
policies.
</P>
<P>
Government departments at all levels have all paid great
attention to the re-education of laid-off women workers and have
cooperated with the labor unions and women's associations in
helping them re-join the job market.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 80 percent of laid-off women workers
received professional re-training in 1998 and that more than 3
million woman workers found jobs via some intermediary agencies.
</P>
<P>
The re-employment rate has thus reached 50 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
