<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- The Cambodian Foreign Ministry sent a letter
Friday to the U.S. Embassy in Cambodia protesting against its
rejection of a check on a shipment of weapon parts said to have
been mistakenly sent to Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The spare parts for U.S.-made M-16 assault rifles was found in
a box Monday when the embassy and the Cambodian Mine Action Center
(CMAC) checked a shipment of medical equipment donated by the
United States to the CMAC, the local newspaper Rasmei Kampuchea
reported Saturday. (Cambodia-U.S.-Weapon Parts)
