NAIROBI -- The Common Market of Eastern and Southern Africa (
COMESA) Council of Ministers has adopted most of the
recommendations drafted by the inter-governmental committee.
</P>
<P>
The proposals include a call to nations to publish a legal
notice on a 90 percent tariff reduction by the end of this year.
So far only Egypt and Madagascar have done so out of 21 COMESA
members, the Daily Nation newspaper reported Saturday. (COMESA-
Proposals)
</P>
