commission for briefing the alliance on Yugoslavia-bound
humanitarian convoys, air deliveries and ground distribution
facilities," the ministry said in a statement. (Russia-UN-NATO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- The scenes of desolation and devastation in Kosovo
are so horrible that NATO needs to suspend its bombing campaign to
try to kick-start peace negotiations, Canadian parliamentarian
Svend Robinson said after a quick tour of the war-torn province.
</P>
<P>
The Canada's New Democratic Party MP, who initially supported
the air war when it began on March 24, now believes that the cause
of the displaced Kosovo Albanians is best served by a pause in the
attacks, the Globe and Mail newspaper reported Saturday. (Canada-
Kosovo) 
