<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of
Beijing, China, aspires to enhance trade relations with Malaysia,
particularly in the agro-forestry sector.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Municipal Agro-Forestry Office's deputy director Nie
Yuzao told reporters here Saturday that most of the business
transactions between Beijing and Malaysia involved mainly palm
oil, textiles, machinery and tools, while the trade volume for
other agricultural products was still insignificant.
</P>
