Malaysia has improved to about 100 million U.S. dollars per year,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Trade was slightly affected last year due to the regional
economic crisis but the situation has returned back to normal,
said Nie who is leading a 55-member trade delegation from
Beijing's agro-forestry industry on a five-day visit to Selangor
beginning May 20.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the visit would will strengthen the economic ties
between Malaysia and China.
</P>
<P>
