MADRID, May 22 (Xinhua) -- World number two Lindsay Davenport
got high boost for the French Open from a 6-1, 6-3 victory over
Paola Suarez in the final of the Madrid Open women's tennis
tournament on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The American need just 55 minutes to wrap up the warm-up
victory over the Argentine in the 180,000-U.S.-dollar clay court
tournament.
</P>
<P>
This is the second WTA title of the year after victory at
Sydney in January. 
</P>
