<HEADLINE> New TV Drama About Han Dynasty Emperor's Epics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The epic adventures of Liu Bang,
the first emperor of the Han Dynasty (206 B.C.- A.D.220), are to
be featured in a 34-episode television series to be broadcast by
China Central TV (CCTV) starting on May 27.
</P>
<P>
Liu Bang, one of the significant names in Chinese history, won
the battle for control of the monarchy over a much more powerful
opponent, Xiang Yu by extraordinary strategies.
</P>
<P>
The TV series, entitled "Liu Bang of the Han Dynasty", will
follow the story of Liu from being a nobody to the leader of the
farmers' uprising against the tyranny of the Qin Dynasty (221-207
B.C.) to his final triumph in establishing the Western Han Dynasty.
</P>
<P>
Co-sponsored by CCTV, Changchun Film Studio and Xuzhou
Municipal Government in Jiangsu Province, the series has taken two
years to shoot.
</P>
<P>
CCTV will broadcast the series via its newly set up 8th channel
which is exclusively for drama. 
</P>
</TEXT>
