<HEADLINE> China Publishes Collection of Bronzeware </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- An acclaimed 16-volume collection
focusing on Chinese bronzeware was finally completed by the
Publishing House of Cultural Relics today.
</P>
<P>
The collection of color plate photographs, featuring more than
3,000 pieces of marvelous ancient bronzeware, has taken seven
years to compile.
</P>
<P>
The collection gives a grand view of the history of Chinese
bronzeware and is of both artistic and archaeological value,
according to local archeologists.
</P>
<P>
The development of Chinese bronzeware has a history of more
than 3,000 years. A number of fine bronze works have been
collected by cultural institutions both at home and abroad.
</P>
