<HEADLINE> Ten Climbers Scale Mount Qomolangma in Spring Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A total of 10 climbers scaled Mount
Qomolangma, the world's highest peak, from the north ridge of
China in the spring season, according to the Tibetan
Mountaineering Association.
</P>
<P>
These climbers were from Ukraine, Poland, Belgium and the
United States. the Ukraine team was the first to conquer the peak
when three climbers reached the 8,848-meter high mount on May 8.
However, one climber died during the descent after they reached
the peak.
</P>
<P>
The Polish and the Belgian teams successfully scaled the peak
on May 18 with one climber died on the way to returning to the
camp.
</P>
<P>
Two Americans also triumphed in climbing and left the base camp
for home Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the association, a total of 170 climbers from 11
foreign teams are attempting to climb Mount Qomolangma during the
spring season. some teams are still staying at the camps at the
6500 meters, preparing for their final attempts. 
</P>
