<HEADLINE> Arab League Keen on Promoting Arab Unity: Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League has exerted constant
efforts in promoting unity and cooperation among the Arab
countries and helping resolve regional disputes peacefully, a
visiting Chinese leader said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Arab League Secretary General Esmat
Abdel-Meguid, Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) Li Ruihuan
hailed the 22-nation pan-Arab forum as one of the most important
regional organizations in the world.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the Arab League will further play a key role in
the regional and international affairs through exerting its unique
influence," said Li, who arrived here on Friday to pay a six-day
official visit to Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The friendship between China and the Arab countries was
nurtured in their common efforts of struggle against imperialism
and colonialism for national liberation, and has been getting deep
in long-term cooperation, Li Ruihuan said.
</P>
<P>
Developing the Sino-Arab friendly cooperation in the current
world situation is the same desire of the Chinese people and the
Arab people, Li stressed.
</P>
<P>
"My current visit is aimed at further strengthening mutual
understanding and friendship, increasing consensus and bolstering
cooperation," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan said the Middle East region has been one of the main
hot spots in the world for the past half a century. Although the
Mideast peace process has been kicked off after the end of the
cold war, regional peace has yet to be realized, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We support peace and justice, dialog and cooperation, and
oppose the use of force and threat to use force in the
region," Li said.
</P>
<P>
China maintains the concerned parties should carry out the
signed peace agreements in a bid to push the peace process
forward on the basis of the relevant United Nations resolutions
and the land-for-peace principle, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
China enjoys friendly cooperation with the Mideast countries,
willing to work persistently with the world community to help
realize comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the region, the
Chinese leader said.
</P>
<P>
Esmat Abdel-Meguid, the Arab League chief, briefed Li Ruihuan
on the latest developments of the Mideast situation, expressing
gratitude to and appreciation for China's constant support for
the Arab just cause.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid said that he agreed to Li's evaluation of the
Arab-Chinese relations, expressing hope that the relations will
be further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Li Ruihuan visits Egypt, the
fourth and last leg of his Asian and African tour which also took
him to South Korea, the United Arab Emirates and Oman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
