<HEADLINE> African Telecoms Summit to Be Held in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 NAIROBI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A summit on African Computing and
 Telecommunications will be held at St John's College in
Cambridge, United Kingdom, from August 25 to 27.
</P>
<P>
 The summit, which will be attended by more than 300 computing
and telecommunications users, dealers, consultants and
policy-makers, will be characterized by lectures, discussions,
workshops and social activities, the Ghana News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
 Under the theme ''Planning beyond the Millennium", the summit
is being organized by the African Information Technology
Exhibitions and Conferences (AITEC), a leading computer magazine
publisher.
</P>
<P>
 AITEC has been instrumental in creating awareness in
Information Technology (IT) in a number of African countries over
the past decade.
</P>
<P>
 Sean Moroney, head of AITEC, said in a statement issued
Thursday that the summit would be the largest and the most
representative gathering of Africa's IT community ever to be held.
</P>
<P>
 It will be an unprecedented opportunity for users and vendors
to meet, exchange information and views, and benefit from an
extensive education program of presentations and workshops, he
said.
</P>
<P>
 There will also be an exhibition that will provide delegates
with the opportunity to meet suppliers and manufacturers who are
active on the African market, and share their concerns and needs
in preparing for the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
 More than 60 speakers, many of them leaders in their field,
are expected to make presentations or lead workshops on key topics
in information technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
