<HEADLINE> Chinese Troops Clear More Mines along Sino-Vietnamese Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese troops have finished the
second stage of a landmine sweep along the Sino-Vietnamese border
and have so far cleared more than 550,000 mines and 200,000
explosives.
</P>
<P>
A team of 510 men under the Yunnan Provincial Military Area
Command started the project on December 1, 1997 and concluded on
March 26 this year, nine months ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
They cleared 117 mine fields in 109.7 square kilometers in six
counties along the border, reclaiming 9200 hectares of farmland
and forests as well as reopening a 27-kilometer-long border
highway and 52 border passes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
