<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Holds Talks with Speaker of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) Li Ruihuan on Saturday held talks with Speaker
of the Egyptian Shura (Consultative) Council Mustafa Kamal Helmy.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Li said China and Egypt have been sharing
sincere and solid friendship on the basis of mutual respect and
understanding since they set up diplomatic ties more than 40 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
Terming China and Egypt as influential developing countries in
the international and regional arenas, Li underlined the two sides
should strengthen unity and cooperation in a bid to set an example
for promoting unity and cooperation among the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Beijing always views Cairo as its close friend and the most
important partner in the Arab world and Africa, Li
stressed.
</P>
<P>
Helmy said in the talks that the relations between Egypt and
China are quite good, adding the Egyptian people are sincere
friends of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
President Hosni Mubarak attaches great importance to developing
Egyptian-Chinese relations, Helmy said, adding the two countries
should constantly exchange high-level visits to promote the
bilateral cooperation, including that between the Egyptian Shura
Council and the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
He expressed conviction that the current visit by Li Ruihuan
to Egypt will contribute more to the development of the bilateral
ties.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan said that China and Egypt are both countries with
ancient civilizations, having made great and unique contributions
to the mankind and social progress.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the importance to enhance the productivity and
raise people's living standard, and preserve the national
characteristics through reforms in the countries like both China
and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
He called for closer cooperation in the fields of economy,
technology and culture in the world, voicing hope that China and
Egypt will learn from each other and promote friendship in the
process of modernization.
</P>
<P>
Helmy said that both Egypt and China are paying great attention
to preserving national characteristics in the process of
modernization and the two sides should strengthen cooperation in
this regard.
</P>
<P>
Li said the CPPCC and the Egyptian Shura Council enjoy good
relations and have helped promote the ties between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan arrived in Cairo on Friday for a six-day official
visit. This is the first time he visits Egypt, the fourth and
last stop of his Asian and African tour which also took him to
South Korea, the United Arab Emirates and Oman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
