<HEADLINE> China Tourism Fair closes in Southwest China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 20 (Xinhua) -- The '99 China Domestic Tourism Fair
closed today in the well-known tourism city of Kunming, capital of
Yunnan Province in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
According to the organizing committee, participants at the
annual fair, including those from Hong Kong and Macao, set up 1,
282 exhibition booths, a 50 percent increase from last year.
</P>
<P>
During the three day fair, 22,000 cooperative contracts were
inked, worth more than 600 million yuan which exceeds the six
previous fairs.
</P>
<P>
Tourism in recent years has been one of China's fastest
growing sectors, whose income last year grew 10.2 percent over the
previous year with international tourism up 3.4 percent and
domestic tourism up 13.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The fair is sponsored by the China National Tourism
Administration and the Yunnan Provincial Government.
</P>
<P>
Kunming is playing host to the '99 International Horticulture
Exposition, the last gardening gala of this century.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is expecting a record 10 million domestic and overseas
tourists in Kunming and the rest of the province during the garden
show, which opened on May 1 and will last through October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
