<HEADLINE> New Sino-U.S. Shipping Route Opened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A direct ocean shipping route,
connecting the port of Xiamen in east China's Fujian province and
the ports of Long Beach and Oakland along the west coast of the
United States, opened today.
</P>
<P>
 The China Ocean Shipping Company(COSCO), the major cargo
carrier on the new route, plans to send one cargo ship every
Saturday to America, with the one way journey lasting 18 days.
</P>
<P>
 There has been no direct route for a long time which meant
that cargo from southeastern China had to be shipped via other
ports in the U.S., which greatly increased the transportation cost.
</P>
<P>
 With the rapid development of the local economy over the past
decade, more and more products, such as toys, shoes, furniture and
sports equipment, are exported to the U.S., which made it more
urgent to open up a new shipping route.
</P>
</TEXT>
