<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti, Lebanese PMs Discuss Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Crown Prince and Prime
Minister Saad Abdullah Al-Sabah met here Saturday with Lebanese
Prime Minister Salim Al-Hoss who arrived earlier in the day for a
two-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
Both sides discussed means of boosting bilateral relations and
issues of mutual concern, the Kuwait News Agency reported. But
the agency did not offer further details about the meeting.
</P>
<P>
However, according to remarks Al-Hoss made to the Kuwaiti press
before the visit, Israel's unconditional withdrawal from South
Lebanon and the reconstruction program of war-torn Lebanon would
top the bilateral talks.
</P>
<P>
Al-Hoss, also Lebanon's foreign minister, said he would "ask
for Kuwait's support to Lebanon in its efforts to press Israel
into halting its aggressions against the land and people of
Lebanon."
</P>
<P>
The Lebanese prime minister was also scheduled to hold talks
with officials of the Kuwait Fund for Arab Economic Development as
well as Kuwaiti businessmen for exchanging views on the economic
situation in Lebanon, apparently with the aim to woo more Kuwaiti
investments for Lebanon's reconstruction and economic development
projects.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time Al-Hoss visits Kuwait since he took
office from his predecessor Rafik Hariri last December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
