<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Import White Maize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- South Africa will have to
import white maize from international markets this year, the
Agriculture Department said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The exact number of maize import is not available. However, the
South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) quoted officials of
the department as saying that the local maize harvest this year
will be six million tons, one million tons less than last year.
</P>
<P>
This will be insufficient to meet local demand, and white
maize will have to be imported from overseas markets, a spokesman
for the department said, adding the import will apparently
increase domestic price of maize meal.
</P>
<P>
Yellow maize may have to meet the demands of the millions of
South African people whose staple food is white maize.  
</P>
