<HEADLINE> Special Fund to Be Set Up to Commemorate Killed Journalists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The China Charity Federation, the
country's largest charitable organization, has decided to
establish a permanent fund to commemorate the three Chinese
journalists killed by the U.S.-led NATO attack on the Chinese
Embassy in Yugoslavia on May 7.
</P>
<P>
The fund, titled "Memorial Fund Dedicated to Shao Yunhuan, Xu
Xinghu and Zhu Ying", is to be set up at the suggestion of both
Chinese people and foreign friends, sources from the federation
said.
</P>
<P>
On May 7, U.S.-led NATO forces fired three missiles at the
Chinese Embassy in Belgrade, killing Shao from the Xinhua News
Agency and the couple of Xu and Zhu from Beijing-based Guangming
Daily newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that funds donated by individuals and work
units from at home and abroad will be used to help the family
members of the victims, the development of social undertakings of
the three's hometowns and to award excellent journalists.
</P>
<P>
A supervision committee comprising of the federation, Xinhua
News Agency, Guangming Daily, family members of the victims and
donators will be set up to manage the use of the funds.
</P>
<P>
The NATO bombing also wounded 20 others and severely damaged
the embassy buildings. This has sparked furious protests and
condemnations around the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
