<HEADLINE> Hebei Closes Foreign Trade, Economic Cooperation Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Hebei Provincial Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Trade Fair closed today in
Shijiazhuang, the capital of Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
During the six-day fair, 559 cooperation contracts for using
direct foreign investment have been signed, involving a total
investment of 2.29 billion U.S. dollars, with contractual use of
foreign investment amounting to 1.5 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to Cai Limin, deputy governor of the province,
overseas investment is mainly channeled into the transportation,
power, chemicals, machine-building and other infrastructure
sectors.
</P>
<P>
