<HEADLINE> Philippine President Promises No Cabinet Revamp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
said Saturday he would not revamp his cabinet which he said is
responsible for his administration's "remarkable progress in the
economy and in peace and order."
</P>
<P>
Estrada said in a radio-TV interview that he continued to have
confidence in all members of his cabinet who are "performing
well."
</P>
<P>
"I have confidence in my cabinet members. They continue to
perform well, and we can see results," he said.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said the country has attained improvements in many
fields, particularly in economics and peace and order, thanks to
his "hardworking" cabinet.
</P>
<P>
"My cabinet's performance is good, so why will I replace its
members," he said.
</P>
<P>
Calls for a cabinet revamp surfaced anew following media
reports linking the heads of the Departments of Interior and Local
Governments (DILG) and Environment and Natural Resources (DENR) to
controversies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
