<HEADLINE> China, Czech Stress Political Solution of Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen and
visiting Czech Foreign Minister Jan Kavan both stressed here
Saturday that the war in Kosovo should end at an early date and
that the Kosovo issue can only be resolved through peaceful
political means.
</P>
<P>
The two reached the consensus during a meeting here Saturday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Kavan said that the Czech new government upholds the "one China
" principle stand, and is ready to further promote relations with
China, especially in the economic and trade areas.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice-premier said that China is also willing to
make joint efforts with the Czech side to cultivate bilateral
relations under the principle of mutual respect, equality and
mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
The Czech foreign minister arrived here Thursday on a four-day
official visit to China at the invitation of his Chinese
counterpart Tang Jiaxuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
