<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Defends Africa on Graft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Corruption is a worldwide problem
which must not only be blamed on Africans, Kenyan President Daniel
arap Moi said.
</P>
<P>
The Daily Nation newspaper Saturday quoted Moi as saying that
the developed countries practised corruption through more
disguised means.
</P>
<P>
"Where does one draw the line between lobbying and corruption
as we see it practised in the West?" Moi questioned Friday after
he opened an exhibition that will be on as part of the event for
the on-going meetings of the Common Market for the Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA).
</P>
<P>
The president said corruption changed its meaning and
connotations from one society to the other and challenged Kenya's
Anti-corruption Authority to come up with clear definitions of
activities that amount to corruption.
</P>
<P>
Such definitions should be based on cultural practices of
different tribes in the country, he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
