<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Northern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.2 degrees
on the open-ended Richter scale on Saturday jolted the vicinity of
Semnan, capital of Iran's northern province of Semnan.
</P>
<P>
The Islamic Republic News Agency reported the quake occurred
at 0010 hours local time Saturday (1940 GMT Friday).
</P>
<P>
The Geophysics Institute of Tehran University registered the
epicenter of the tremor some 40 kilometers southwest of the
provincial capital of Semnan.
</P>
<P>
Reports of possible casualties or damage are not immediatley
available.
</P>
<P>
Two strong earthquakes measuring at 6.8 and 5.9 degrees rocked
Iran's southern province of Fars on May 7, killing 28 people and
injuring more than 100 others. 
