<P>
BANGKOK, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Aeronautical Radio team
stunned the girls of Shanghai Cable TV of China on Friday by
winning the hot favorites 3-2 in the AVC Asian Women's Club
Volleyball Championship held in the northeastern Thai province of
Ubon Ratchathani.
</P>
<P>
Cheered on by an enthusiastic crowd of mostly students, the
Thai club, consisting national players, lost the first set 16-25
but got back on level term by winning a thriller 25-23 thanks to
some great spikes from Anna Paijinda.
</P>
