<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Lodge Protest with NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan lodged a protest with
the NATO against the damage caused to its embassy building as a
result of NATO bombing on Belgrade Thursday night, according to a
Pakistani Foreign Office official.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Office Friday night confirmed reports that some
window-panes of the Pakistan Embassy building were blown out
during the NATO bombardment in the vicinity of diplomatic
missions.
</P>
<P>
However, no loss of life was reported.
</P>
<P>
The Official said the Pakistan Embassy in Belgrade has been
non-functional ever since the Bosnian crisis. Only an assistant
and a security guard are there to safeguard the premises. "Both
are safe and unhurt," he said.
</P>
<P>
The NATO bombing raids have blown out windows of the Swiss,
Swedish, Spanish and Indian embassies in the past two nights,
according to reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
