Cooperation with World Bank
</P>
<P>
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing expressed the hope that the World Bank
and the International Financial Corp. will increase cooperation
with China when meeting with Peter Woicke, managing director of
the World Bank and vice executive president of the International
Financial Corp., and Martin Bouygues, president of the Bouygues
Group of France, on separate occasions Friday.
</P>
<P>
Investigation of NATO Bombing Stressed
</P>
<P>
Vice-President Hu Jintao told a Revolutionary Party of Tanzania
delegation Friday that US-led NATO needs to take full
responsibility for the attack on the Chinese Embassy in Belgrade
and to give a full explanation in response to the Chinese
government's demand.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao urged the
NATO to investigate the case of the attack on China's embassy and
make public the result of the investigation at an early date.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Zhu said time was not ripe for an U.S. envoy to come
to China. He denied the saying that military exchanges between
China and the United States will be resumed next month.
</P>
