<HEADLINE> Weekly Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin on Thursday expressed his hope
that through joint efforts, there will be a smooth transition and
handover of Macao to China.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Portuguese Foreign Minister Jaime Gama,
Jiang said China will handle Macao affairs in strict accordance
with the Macao Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan held talks with
Gama and said there will be a smooth transfer of power in Macao as
long as China and Portugal work together and adhere to the
declaration and consider Macao's actual conditions.
</P>
<P>
Gama said on Thursday that he believed there will be an
appropriate and smooth transition of Macao and that Portugal and
China will provide the world with an example of common
understanding.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, FM Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said that the election of the
Macao Special Administration Region Chief Executive candidate has
demonstrated the principles of fairness, impartiality, openness,
democracy and honesty.
</P>
<P>
 Exchange Between Chinese, Vietnamese Communist Parties
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji, in Wednesday's meeting with Nguyen Tan Dung,
Political Bureau member of the Communist Party of Viet Nam Central
Committee and Standing Deputy Prime Minister, expressed the hope
that both sides would exchange views on the theory and practice of
socialist construction during the current visit so as to deepen
mutual understanding, trust and friendship, and push forward
socialist construction and reform of both countries.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo also met with the visitor.
</P>
<P>
 China, Australia Economic Cooperation Important
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu Rongji Monday expressed the hope that Australia
would create more favorable investment conditions so as to boost
new progress of cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Australian Deputy Prime Minister and
Minister for Trade Tim Fischer, Zhu said bilateral cooperation in
various sectors have expanded continuously and achieved good
results, and Australia has become one of China's most important
countries for investment.
</P>
<P>
Fischer said that Australia is encouraged by the constructive
progress in the Australia-China talks on the latter's WTO
accession.
</P>
