<HEADLINE> Venezuela: Imports Increase in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's imports reached 14.016
billion dollars last year, up 7.7 percent over 1997.
</P>
<P>
Statistics and Informatics Central Office data shows imports
from the United States amounted to 45.9 percent of the total,
which is equivalent to 6.497 billion U.S dollars.
</P>
<P>
Imports from Colombia dropped 3.7 percent, from 862 million
dollars in 1997, to 830 million dollars in 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, Colombia is still the second largest exporter to
Venezuela, with figures reaching 5.9 percent of the total,
followed by Japan with 4.7 percent, Mexico with 4.5 percent,
Brazil with 4.5 percent, Germany with 4.3 percent, and Italy with
3.7 percent.
</P>
