<DOCNO> XIE19990522.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Caring For Old People In East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Old people are getting better care
in China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that there are more than 5.5 million
people at and above 60 in the province, accounting for 12.5
percent of its population, with an average life expectancy of 72.5,
close to that of developed countries.
</P>
<P>
All cities, counties and townships in Zhejiang have special
offices to handle problems of the elderly, officials say, and more
than 800,000 people now have old-age pensions.
</P>
<P>
The province has also set up nearly 2,000 retirement homes for
elderly persons who have no relatives or who prefer to live alone,
and more than 23,000 recreation centers and 1,040 special schools
for them.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang has spent 732 million yuan on welfare facilities for
the elderly since 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
