<HEADLINE> Colombian Senator Kidnapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Colombian Senator Piedad
Cordoba de Castro, of the opposition Liberal Party, was kidnapped
Friday in Medellin, the capital of the Antioquia department, by a
group of unidentified gunmen, local authorities said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian congresswoman was kidnapped in El Poblado, a high-
income residential sector in the southeast of the city.
</P>
<P>
Local media reports quoted eyewitnesses as saying that at least
15 men grabbed Cordoba inside a clinic where she was visiting
someone in the exclusive neighborhood of El Poblado.
</P>
<P>
Cordoba is a member of a congressional peace commission and has
reportedly met several times with leaders of a leftist rebel group
over the last few weeks.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the kidnapping.
</P>
<P>
Media reports also quoted the kidnappers as saying that the
taking of Cordoba was intended to send a "peace message" to the
government.
</P>
<P>
After a stalemate of several months, peace negotiations between
the government and the leftist Revolutionary Armed Forces of
Colombia (FARC) resumed earlier this month. 
</P>
