<TEXT>
<P>
ZEGRAB, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Croatian President Franjo Tudjman
proposed Thursday that the international community should find a
solution to the Kosovo crisis acceptable to all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
He called for an end to the Balkan war that has caused severe
economic losses to many countries.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman made the proposal when meeting with some foreign
ambassadors to Croatia, according to the Croatian Broadcasting
Television.
</P>
<P>
He noted that a settlement of the Kosovo issue should take into
account the fact that Kosovo, a Serbian province that is mostly
populated by ethnic Albanians who have been seeking for
independence, is the historical cradle of the nation of Serbia.
</P>
<P>
A solution to the conflict should be acceptable to all parties
involved, he added.
</P>
<P>
Since NATO began air attacks against Yugoslavia on March 24,
transportation through Yugoslavia to neighboring countries has
been cut and an exodus of Kosovar refugees crossed Yugoslav
borders, causing a lot of social problems and economic losses to
the nearby countries. 
</P>
