<HEADLINE> Rafter Beats Sampras to Lead Australia into Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Rafter beat Pete Sampras 6-3,
7-5 with an exciting display of attacking tennis on Friday to
steer Australia into the final of the World Team Cup in
duesseldorf, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, who has now won the last three matches he has played
against Sampras, handed Australia a winning 2-0 lead over the
United States to clinch a place in Saturday's final against Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Mark Philippoussis had earlier put the Australians ahead with a
hard-fought 6-4,, 6-7, 7-5 win over veteran Richey Reneberg.
</P>
<P>
Rafter and Sampras, respectively third and second in the ATP
Tour rankings, had met 11 times before with the American leading 8-
3.
</P>
<P>
Philippoussis was made to work hard by Reneberg, a modest 291st
in the world and who was only called into singles duty after Andre
Agassi pulled out with a shoulder injury earlier in the event.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other tie, Slovakia blanked France 3-0. Karol
Kucera first crushed Guillaume Raoux 6-3, 6-2 and Dominik Hrbaty
then beat Nicolas Escude 6-4, 3-6, 6-4. Dominik Hrbaty teamed
with Tomas Catar to defeat Guillaume Raoux and Nicolas Escude 6-4,
6-2 to seal the win. 
</P>
