<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada said Friday that a
peso-dollar exchange rate of 37:1 signifies a stable local
currency that would be ideal in striking a balance between the
concerns of domestic businesses and the export sector.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Post:
</P>
<P>
-- The Moro Islamic Liberation Front said Friday that it will
agree to hold peace talks with the government inside the
Philippines instead of abroad as it had earlier demanded.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star:
</P>
<P>
-- The Central Bank of the Philippines will slash its overnight
borrowing and lending rates by another 12.5 basis points to 9.875
percent and 11.875 percent Monday. 
</P>
