<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Cuts Key Rates for 15th Time This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of the Philippines
will cut its overnight borrowing and lending rates by another 12.5
basis points to 9.875 percent and 11.875 percent respective
Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement published here Saturday, the central bank said
that this is the 15th time this year it adjusted the rates
downward in order to "help sustain the recovery of the stock
market and encourage the resumption of credit growth."
</P>
<P>
The cumulative reduction the central bank made since the start
of this year totals 350 basis points.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here said the lower overnight rates are expected to
provide more money supply to fuel economic activities.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said it was possible to reduce its key rates
further due to the absence of inflationary pressure and despite
its rate cut, capital inflow will remain strong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
