<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Martinez Increases Lead in Midi Libre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Alberto Martinez remained on
course to win the Midi Libre race after the fourth stage on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Euskatel rider increased his lead to two minutes and 26
seconds in front of second-placed Alexander Vinokurov of
Kazakhstan after the 184 kilometers stage from Perpignan to
Beziers.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Benoit Salmon won the stage by 55 seconds from his
Casino team mate Vinokurov, winner of Wednesday's second stage,
with compatriot Stephane Heulot of La Francaise des Jeux third.
</P>
<P>
Martinez has held the lead since the first stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
