<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Denmark Share Women's Singles Top Four </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COPENHAGEN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Shuttlers from hosts Denmark and
China each claimed two places in the women's singles semi-finals
event of the World Badminton Championships here Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese players who made the semi-finalists were second
seed Gong Ruina and fourth seed Dai Yun while third seed Camilla
Martin and eighth seed Mette Sorensen notched up the other two
places for Denmark.
</P>
<P>
Gong Ruina, winner in Swedish Open earlier this year, continued
her wining streak at the tournament, beating Hartono Cindana of
Indonesia 11-3 and 11-2 in 18 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, her compatriot Dai Yun had a hard fight in the
quarter-finals, rallied back from first set down to beat Lee Kyung
Won of South Korea 6-11, 11-5, 11-7.
</P>
<P>
Only after the first set could Dai Yun, who injured her right
thigh in a third round match against Lidya Djaelawidjaya of
Indonesia on Wednesday, find back her form and took two sets in a
row for the victory.
</P>
<P>
"I had to fight pain and tiredness in the match," said Dai Yun,
who had a immediate therapy of her injury after she left the court.
</P>
<P>
Camilla, top favourite from the host country, continued to
enjoy an easy path en route to her goal of the gold medal Friday
evening when she beat Zhang Ning 11-9, 11-7 in 30 minutes.
</P>
<P>
"I have been enjoying the tournament now," said Martin, who
lost to China's Dai Yun in the women's singles at the Sudirman Cup
final last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"I have relaxed and played better and better in the
championships," she added.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Mette Sorensen scored a hard-fought victory in the
quarter-finals, beating Welsh Kelly Morgan 9-11, 13-10, 11-8.
</P>
<P>
Morgan, who will be 24 Saturday, set up her name at the
Championships by eliminating top seed Ye Zhaoying of China in the
first round on Tuesday, making it the first time that a world
champion has been crashed in first round match.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals on Saturday, Martin will take on Gong Ruina
while Sorensen faces Dai Yun for a place in the final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
