<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Friday as investors pondered the next move the Federal Reserve
will take for interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 37.46 at
10,829.28 and Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 8.54 at 1,330.29.
The technology heavy Nasdaq index fell 22.09 at 2,520.14.
</P>
<P>
Investors adjusted their portfolios three days after the
Federal Reserve decided to leave interest rate alone but warned
that more signs of inflation will prompt rise in interest rates.
Investors shifted some shares from big cap stocks to small ones,
thus improving market breadth.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 2.55 at 636.87. But the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 3.34 at 795.37 and
the Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 1.12 at 449.14.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 6-to-5 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,620 up, 1,352 down and
562 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 685.49 million shares from 744.00
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
